Introduction

XD, formerly known as XEED, is a five-member boy group. Originally consisting of four members (Doha, Roni, Bao, and Jaemin) they made their debut on December 1, 2022, with the mini album "Dreamland". Just a month after their debut, it was announced that member Roni would be leaving the group for personal reasons.

With the announcement of their first comeback, "Blue", two new members were revealed. Former TST member UO and along with former TARGET member Shun.

While the group initially disbanded on April 8th of 2024, all five members shared a "XD" logo, along with a new Instagram account, announcing that the group will be resuming activities under the name XD on the 20th of April 2025.
